"Your Systems" means applications, services, networks, and infrastructure
owned or operated by Your Organization primarily for Your Organization's own
business or internal purposes. A system is not Your System merely because a
third party has authorized You to test it.

"Internal Performance Testing" means creating, debugging, validating, or
executing performance, load, stress, reliability, or related tests solely
against Your Systems and solely for Your Organization's own internal quality
assurance, engineering, security, or operational purposes.

"Testing Service Provider" means a person or entity that, as a material part
of its business, performs or manages performance, load, stress, reliability,
or related testing for third parties, whether as consultancy, staff
augmentation, managed testing, testing as a service, or otherwise.

"Testing Platform Provider" means a person or entity that, as a material part
of its business, provides a product, platform, cloud service, hosted service,
managed service, extension, plugin, or other offering for creating, executing,
managing, or analyzing performance, load, stress, reliability, or related
tests.

"Restricted Provider" means a Testing Service Provider or Testing Platform
Provider.

"Community Limits" means any technical or quantitative limits expressly
identified in the Software or in the release-specific documentation supplied
with the Software at the time You receive it, including limits on concurrent
threads, virtual users, executions, duration, throughput, or requests per
second. If no Community Limit is stated for a metric in a particular release,
